{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F01-v113-terminal-failure-scope","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The v1.13 terminal diagnosis is confined to non-performance verifier-role and custody evidence: a canonical live-bundle verifier rejected the preserved report in the sole binding attempt, which was outer-finalized before any formal launch; v1.14 does not resume or reuse v1.13 evidence."},{"id":"F02-explicit-canonical-and-bound-roles","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Binding creation explicitly applies the path-exclusive canonical report verifier, while the independent strict binding consumer explicitly applies a distinct package-local preserved-report verifier; the ambiguous shared entry point was removed."},{"id":"F03-fixed-bound-report-contract","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The preserved role independently enforces the fixed report schema, exact ten-command order and argv, QA/runtime/Git/input identities, accepted-closure semantics, complete command-10 inventory and conformance semantics, and exact 20-stream custody without weakening the canonical role."},{"id":"F04-package-local-custody","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The preserved verifier reads only safe single-link binding siblings, rejects missing, changed, symlinked, hardlinked, duplicate, reordered, noncanonical, or unreferenced preformal evidence, permits declared non-preformal sidecars, and never reopens recorded ambient origin files."},{"id":"F05-review-seal-and-json-type-parity","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Exact canonical repository/input/review paths, prospective-review manifest and findings, runtime-seal fields and Python version, command ordinals, command-9 empty stderr, and strict JSON scalar types are cross-linked to the binding; adversarial Boolean and rehashed substitutions are rejected."},{"id":"F06-single-capture-publication","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Binding creation canonical-verifies the original report, captures the report and all 20 log payloads once under stable inode custody, checks byte identity after verification, and publishes only those captured bytes, closing the prior origin-reopen and publication-time mutation seam."},{"id":"F07-real-producer-consumer-regression","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The permanent regression generates a canonical report and 20 streams after finalizing inventory, audit, review, and seal identities; copies all 21 files byte-identically; requires real root-schema binding creation followed by the untouched strict verify_binding consumer; and asserts the verified object equals the created object."},{"id":"F08-preseal-and-formal-root-operations","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The operator runbook scans every ignored v1.14 lifecycle and hidden-claim namespace both before and after the aggregate gates, validates the exact command-10 object and recomputable identities before development, and exclusively creates and fsyncs the binding-hash formal parent required by ProducerAttempt before the sole formal launch."},{"id":"F09-fresh-seed-and-prior-domain-arithmetic","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"Independent verifier paths regenerate 10 unique current masters and 1,360 current streams and compare them with 130 prior masters and 17,680 prior streams through v1.13, with zero internal or cross-domain overlap in every master/stream class."},{"id":"F10-scientific-continuity","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"All 17 sealed scientific protocol blocks retain canonical SHA-256 fa44fd93a672db3905d45a0e99c568985e7e2e5d02d32043c830db413005a5c3; model.py, learning.py, planning.py, and runtime_lane.py retain their sealed identities; raw-result v9 and formal-binding v10 representations remain unchanged."},{"id":"F11-same-wheel-runtime-closure","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Fresh QA and runtime environments install the same non-editable Prospect wheel identity; the runtime has exactly the 45-row locked closure and no pytest, Ruff, or mypy distribution; QA has those tools; installed source and dependency identities remain mandatory pre-outcome gates."},{"id":"F12-one-shot-lifecycle-custody","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Fresh version-owned seal, development, audit, closure, preformal, binding, formal, formal-audit, semantic-review, and adjudication paths use no-replace claims, same-inode outer completions where required, and explicit terminal boundaries that forbid same-version repair, resume, or retry after consumption."},{"id":"F13-assurance-boundary","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"Protocol, seal, binding, operator, audit, and adjudication identities bind prospect.wm001.trust-model.v1 with tamper resistance and external attestation explicitly false; stable reads and cooperative locking are not overstated as hostile-writer protection."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1638,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"2506f76068d29d6862f50a15b619da7f9ab6c8507239c06c0b6f2a2f07c6346c"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistemic/maturity.py","sha256":"2a81abe60f12285f66f2bcd351589de28851412f1d9df7f2003843a845a2510e"},{"bytes":13611,"path":"bench/epistemic/problem.py","sha256":"c66ae13d3e833ffd1be1562a89e0e9035d6197b95723179b930c1ca2a1059c66"},{"bytes":1097,"path":"bench/epistemic/run_maturity.py","sha256":"86ae2c3175262f559a274827c96c30212fbdb9250e3a4614f92c861b7498feb7"},{"bytes":20656,"path":"bench/epistemic/runtim